Jzq6ccJZDZFOSiPHAgEx-qXBFdAw0xz6GNtuez9jbjqTK0TbxhKtxB_pvRlCiZ-RXCck58NpZOrhUIPfV5NqOOSos4MfyW2TwfaRhYWOTl9hdwjzDcYB3GfxXYzC5yKF2HVKi3Ywpw8ZaC-KS3_rAV4gOd8K-GMKJj_-oy21EGYvkuo5kIemilWSiz5FTrXxLEocYM7agA6kZJfzcWYZ7jmA18s0nsLLZsKGUdjrQ6AK4U2yvaCR0p95w7MrnjP4VrW95ndo_RYlxDFFXR8SuB4mNbs9eQNrerzuw0lmzoHOuJwMsX8WjweF0HTzWek9cepvmdKRXJciEOljOk1Sdh8m1s4DFBCrpLkK9vFQ4Ds19BgxJJad9quzBwSj-kl4PIETQwBu6LKeukOVaBWTtBsA_I-miFLhQwl5wHjMrAGA-3Kw3hLMY1h3YB8_3mfiVM-B1awpOewPzjoWukQCv7RO3UfAiXWi8rGjOgb5QnVMaPv7bWeem5eqvXp-mMDQAPUCF7tWcPOlzVJjYN1xqjsOH1h0ZoOcl5Ayc-KYjbR4pf0xDeUoPcyK1kt0u6-tJ9o8vhiVbFvU900PxwJCu3IzRNirWJBiTvHI0vdrK0wKE4EyyriOtpg-S6kclS_xbPGHg==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring abstract class use**\\n\\nI'm considering using an abstract class here for simplicity. I want to create a static class called SampleOperations that has methods like describe and combine. I’m also wondering if I should override the toString method. It's interesting that getMethods reveals toString as part of SampleOperations, not from Object. Since I'm declaring the class, I need to ensure that InterfaceMaker adds it properly while avoiding any confusion with generic Object names.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_bPkqr7E8mVtRAPTqIOWe9aVU|fc_012fc9f2860bd5f60169fb7e51c8d481a298cf9b58dd17766d", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/cglib/cglib-nodep/2.2.2/src/test/java/cglib/cglib_nodep/InterfaceMakerTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage cglib.cglib_nodep;\n\nimport java.io.IOException;\nimport java.lang.reflect.Method;\n\nimport net.sf.cglib.core.CodeGenerationException;\nimport net.sf.cglib.proxy.InterfaceMaker;\nimport org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class InterfaceMakerTest {\n\n    @Test\n    void createsInterfaceFromPublicMethodsOnClass() throws Exception {\n        InterfaceMaker maker = new InterfaceMaker();\n        maker.add(SampleOperations.class);\n\n        try {\n            Class<?> generatedInterface = maker.create();\n\n            assertThat(generatedInterface.isInterface()).isTrue();\n            assertThat(generatedInterface.getMethods()).extracting(Method::getName)\n                    .contains(\"describe\", \"combine\");\n            assertThat(generatedInterface.getMethod(\"describe\", String.class).getExceptionTypes())\n                    .containsExactly(IOException.class);\n            assertThat(generatedInterface.getMethod(\"combine\", int.class, int.class).getReturnType())\n                    .isEqualTo(int.class);\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n                throw error;\n            }\n        } catch (CodeGenerationException exception) {\n            Error error = findUnsupportedFeatureError(exception);\n            if (error == null) {\n                throw exception;\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static Error findUnsupportedFeatureError(Throwable throwable) {\n        Throwable current = throwable;\n        while (current != null) {\n            if (current instanceof Error error && NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n                return error;\n            }\n            current = current.getCause();\n        }\n        return null;\n    }\n\n    public static class SampleOperations {\n        public String describe(String value) throws IOException {\n            return \"value: \" + value;\n        }\n\n        public int combine(int left, int right) {\n            return left + right;\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 788, "output": 1476, "cacheRead": 15360, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 17624, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778089539037, "responseId": "resp_012fc9f2860bd5f60169fb7e43a89481a2af59bd6fab6bdb0f"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_bPkqr7E8mVtRAPTqIOWe9aVU|fc_012fc9f2860bd5f60169fb7e51c8d481a298cf9b58dd17766d", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully wrote 2325 bytes to tests/src/cglib/cglib-nodep/2.2.2/src/test/java/cglib/cglib_nodep/InterfaceMakerTest.java"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1778089557152}]}
